news.title: CAG report flags stamp duty, lease period errors in Karnataka's Sandur
news.para: Comptroller and Auditor General report reveals `13.33 crore shortfall due to incorrect stamp duty collection, lease period reckoning of mines; Rs 34.08 lakh is recovered so far

news.title: Patna: Enforcement directorate attaches properties of Sri Anuanand Construction
news.para: The immovable properties in Patna and Noida are registered in the name of the company and its director Bimal Kumar.

news.title: Pay property tax by December 31 to avoid penalty: Ludhiana civic body chief
news.para: ​​No penalty will be imposed on payment of tax from Oct 1 to Dec 31 while 10% penalty will be imposed on payment of tax from Jan 1 to March 31.

news.title: WeWork India leases 1.26 lakh sq ft office space in Mumbai’s Andheri
news.para: The company will be paying a monthly rental of over Rs 1.38 crore for the office space on the 6th, 7th, and 8th floor of commercial tower Lightbridge in Andheri’s Saki Vihar area, taking the total payout through the entire term to over Rs 87 crore.

news.title: Construction work to be stopped at Byculla and Borivali East to improve AQI: BMC chief
news.para: Making the announcement, Brihanmumbai Municipal Commissioner Bhushan Gagrani on Monday said work will be stopped at private and government construction sites, including those being carried out by the civic body, till the time the AQI improves.

news.title: DDA approves special housing schemes for workers and disadvantaged groups
news.para: The authority has approved launching of three housing schemes, which include 25 per cent discount for building and construction workers, including beneficiaries of PM-Vishwakarma Scheme

news.title: FPCE urges government to act against misleading realty advertisements
news.para: In February, ASCI signed a pact with the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) to monitor and address misleading advertisements in the real estate sector.

news.title: Sunac China wins more support for restructuring from bondholders: Sources
news.para: Sunac China needs approval from holders of all of its 10 onshore bonds worth 15.4 billion yuan ($2.11 billion) to implement the debt restructuring.

news.title: Towards 2047: Key growth catalysts for Atmanirbhar Bharat and Amrut Kaal
news.para: The Make in India initiative is central to India’s economic self-reliance and manufacturing dominance. Metropolitan centers like Chennai, Pune, and Mumbai are evolving into manufacturing hubs through integrated multimodal infrastructure.

news.title: Sebi to auction 23 properties of nine companies in February 2025
news.para: Additionally, GBC Industrial Corporation, Waris Group, Pincon Group, Kolkata Weir Industries Ltd (KWIL), Annex Infrastructure India, I-core Group and MPS Group were the other firms whose properties will also be auctioned.

news.title: Indiramma scheme beneficiaries to get flexibility in design and construction
news.para: Additionally, beneficiaries who have the financial means can exceed the maximum 400 sq ft built space finalised by the govt under the 5 lakh financial assistance Indiramma housing scheme.

news.title: CREST gets Chandigarh administration's nod to install solar panels on 10 marla houses
news.para: Empowered to make decisions and proceed with the implementation, CREST has begun preparing and finalising procedures in coordination with relevant departments of the Chandigarh administration.

news.title: 2024: A transformative year for the office segment
news.para: Flexible workspaces have truly come-of-age in 2024. Occupiers are no longer viewing flex spaces as temporary solutions but as strategic assets that align with hybrid work models.

news.title: Kochi: Infopark Phase III sees land pooling hurdles
news.para: Govt decided to implement the project on 300 acres through land pooling. In this method, the owner will get back 60% of the original land after project implementation, and the value of land will be three to four times more than the original value.

news.title: Odisha RERA directs builders to submit quarterly reports and annual audit certificates
news.para: ORERA issued the direction after noticing that several promoters were not submitting the two reports, which apprise buyers of the latest status of projects.

news.title: Over 141 acres land allocated to set up pharma park in Naya Raipur
news.para: The state govt's representative emphasises that developing Chhattisgarh requires strengthening and making healthcare services more accessible to citizens.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality shares soar nearly 12% in market debut on December 30
news.para: The stock made its debut at Rs 718.15, a surge of 11.68 per cent from the issue price on the BSE. It later jumped 16.45 per cent to Rs 748.80.

news.title: Slum-free Panchkula remains a mere promise
news.para: In the era of ‘Swachh Bharat' initiatives, these slum areas have become hubs of unsanitary conditions, causing trouble not only for the colony dwellers but also for residents in other sectors.
